content: Do you have any jokes about umbrellas?

Sure, here's one for you:

Why don't scientists trust atoms when it rains?

Because they make up everything and can't be trusted to keep their electrons! 

But if you're looking for something more umbrella-specific, how about this:

Why did the umbrella go to school?

Because it wanted to be a little more knowledgeable and less sheltered! 

Hope that brings a smile to your face!
